author: Jack Power
title: Coronavirus: Republic reports 31 further deaths
description: HSE insists testing backlog to be cleared by end of week and is investigating incorrect text messages
content:
A further 31 people have died of the coronavirus in Ireland, the National Public Health Emergency Team has said.
A total of 365 people have now died in the State after contracting Covid-19, figures released on Monday evening state, and a total of 10,647 case… [+5785 chars]
